REPOSITORY STRUCTURE FOR WINDOWS REPAIR TOOLS
=============================================

Create the following folder structure in your GitHub repository:

windows-repair-tools/
│
├── README.md                    # Main repository documentation
├── LICENSE                      # MIT License file
├── CONTRIBUTING.md             # Contribution guidelines
├── .gitignore                  # Git ignore file
│
├── tools/                      # Main tools directory
│   ├── network-repair-tool.bat
│   ├── system-file-repair-tool.bat
│   └── README.md              # Tools directory readme
│
├── docs/                       # Documentation directory
│   ├── usage-guide.md         # Detailed usage instructions
│   ├── troubleshooting.md     # Common issues and solutions
│   ├── changelog.md           # Version history
│   └── screenshots/           # Screenshots folder
│       ├── network-tool-menu.png
│       ├── system-tool-menu.png
│       └── admin-prompt.png
│
├── assets/                     # Repository assets
│   ├── banner.png             # Repository banner image
│   └── icons/                 # Icon files
│       ├── network.ico
│       └── system.ico
│
└── releases/                   # Release packages
    └── v1.0/
        ├── windows-repair-tools-v1.0.zip
        └── checksums.txt

SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
==================

1. Create a new GitHub repository named "windows-repair-tools"

2. Clone the repository locally:
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/windows-repair-tools.git

3. Create the folder structure:
   mkdir tools docs docs/screenshots assets assets/icons releases

4. Add your batch files to the tools/ directory

5. Add all the documentation files created above

6. Create a simple banner.png for the repository (optional)

7. Take screenshots of your tools in action and add to docs/screenshots/

8. Initial commit:
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit: Windows Repair Tools Collection"
   git push origin main

9. Create your first release:
   - Go to GitHub repository
   - Click "Releases" 
   - Click "Create a new release"
   - Tag version: v1.0
   - Release title: "Windows Repair Tools v1.0"
   - Describe the release
   - Attach a zip file with all tools

10. Update README.md links:
    - Replace "yourusername" with your GitHub username
    - Update any broken image links
    - Add actual screenshots

ADDITIONAL FILES TO CREATE:
==========================

1. tools/README.md:
   "This directory contains all the repair tool batch files."

2. docs/changelog.md:
   "# Changelog
   
   ## [1.0.0] - 2024-XX-XX
   ### Added
   - Initial release
   - Network Repair Tool
   - System File Repair Tool"

3. docs/troubleshooting.md:
   "# Troubleshooting Guide
   
   Common issues and their solutions..."

GITHUB REPOSITORY SETTINGS:
==========================

1. Add description: "Collection of Windows repair and maintenance batch scripts"

2. Add topics: 
   - windows
   - batch-script
   - repair-tools
   - network-tools
   - system-maintenance
   - windows-10
   - windows-11
   - troubleshooting

3. Add website: Link to your portfolio (if any)

4. Enable Issues tab for bug reports

5. Create Issue templates:
   - Bug report
   - Feature request
   - Tool suggestion

6. Set up GitHub Pages (optional) for documentation
